Q56: -> About the application: - it would be helpful to receive an confirmation by e-mail that the application was saved (maybe with also the answers the applicant gave). It might have been a bug but it happened at least for two of us - the information about the date of the result was only on the application form? (If not, it was not easily accessible) - very personal opinion here about the algorithm; it is a choice to give the possibility to the applicant to define him/her/its self as belonging to a minority... but it could also give the the tricky choice between "oh i should put more chance on my side" and "i would not like to be chosen against an equivalent applicant JUST because of this". On the deadline day for the application, @Leiden University,  there was a workshop about different discriminations in work environment and how to manage to improve the situation; making the pool of possible applicants more heterogeneous (to include more persons from each minorities in this pool) seems a way "better" solution than "positive discrimination".
